sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Client
    participant AS as AuthShield :8000
    participant VP as VaultPay :8001
    participant Redis as Redis DB 0
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    %% ── Login ──────────────────────────────────────────
    User->>Client: Enter credentials
    Client->>AS: POST /auth/login<br/>{email, password}
    AS->>DB: SELECT user WHERE email = ?
    AS->>AS: bcrypt.verify(password, hash)

    alt Invalid credentials
        AS-->>Client: 401 InvalidCredentialsError
    end

    AS->>AS: jwt.encode(user_id, email, roles, exp)
    AS-->>Client: 200 {access_token, token_type: "bearer"}

    %% ── Authenticated request (fast-path) ───────────────
    Client->>VP: GET /wallets/me<br/>Authorization: Bearer <token>
    VP->>VP: RequestIDMiddleware → X-Request-ID
    VP->>VP: jwt.decode(token, JWT_SECRET_KEY)
    VP->>Redis: GET revoked:{jti}

    alt Token revoked
        Redis-->>VP: EXISTS = true
        VP-->>Client: 401 TokenRevokedError
    end

    VP->>VP: Build UserContext(user_id, roles)
    VP->>DB: SELECT wallet WHERE user_id = ?
    VP-->>Client: 200 {wallet data}

    %% ── Logout / Token revocation ───────────────────────
    User->>Client: Logout
    Client->>AS: POST /auth/logout<br/>Authorization: Bearer <token>
    AS->>AS: Decode token → extract jti, exp
    AS->>Redis: SET revoked:{jti} = 1  EX remaining_ttl
    AS-->>Client: 200 {message: "Logged out"}

    Note over VP,Redis: Next VP request with same token<br/>hits Redis → 401 TokenRevokedError
